%S A393447 1,0,3,3,9,0,8,0,7,2,3,6,2,9,2,3,9,0,9,6
%N A393447 Decimal expansion of the unique solution x > 0 to Sum_{primes p} arcsin(p^-x) = Pi.
%H A393447 Victor Miller, <a href="https://vimeo.com/1179730427">A Difficult Prime Series Problem</a>, Talk in Doron Zeilberger's Experimental Mathematics Seminar, Rutgers University, Apr 02 2026 (Vimeo); <a href="https://sites.math.rutgers.edu/~zeilberg/expmath/miller26.pdf">Slides</a>. This is the constant sigma subscript minus on slide 23.
%e A393447 1.03390807...
%t A393447 FindRoot[Sum[(j+1)*Binomial[2*j+2, j+1] / ((2*j+1)^2 * 2^(2*j+1)) * PrimeZetaP[(2*j + 1)*x], {j, 0, 28}] == Pi, {x, 1.01}, WorkingPrecision -> 50] (* _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Apr 04 2026 *)
